benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/admin/cache/accounts/{accountId} - Invalidates Caches per account level

covered: Valid Deletion: TC01 demonstrates successful cache invalidation for a valid account (204 with empty body) and confirms per account cache invalidation.
Non Existent Resource: TC02, TC16, TC18 cover 404 responses for non existent accounts and edge cases with partially missing data.
Input Validation: TC03, TC12, TC14, TC15 cover invalid accountId formats (400).
Missing Path Parameter: TC04 ensures 404 when accountId is missing from the path.
Authorization: TC05, TC06 cover 401 for missing authentication and expired or invalid tokens.
System Resilience: TC07 and TC17 cover degraded performance and network recovery scenarios (204 or 503).
Dependency Availability: TC08 covers 503 when the cache service is down or unreachable.
Query Parameters Handling: TC09 shows extra query parameters do not affect success (204).
Edge Case - Very Large AccountId: TC10 yields 404 or 400 depending on validation.
Unsupported HTTP Methods: TC11 ensures 405 for unsupported methods.
Performance Concurrency: TC13 tests concurrent DELETEs across multiple accounts with acceptable average response time.
Security: TC14 and TC15 verify input sanitization against SQL injection and XSS, returning 400.
Edge Case - No Accounts: TC16 demonstrates 404 when the system has no accounts.
Edge Variation: Partially populated dataset: TC18 covers 404 for non existent accounts in a partially populated DB.
Backward Compatibility: TC19 confirms no regression with previous DELETE endpoint usage.
gaps: 403 Forbidden authorization tests for authenticated but non-admin users are missing.
Caching headers validation for DELETE responses (Cache-Control, ETag) is not tested.
Single resource concurrency race condition test is not covered.
Trailing slash/path normalization variations are not covered.
Internal server error scenarios (500) are not tested beyond 503 for dependent services.
Idempotency verification for repeated DELETE requests could be explicit.
Observability checks (logs/metrics) around delete operations are not tested.
recommendations: Add 403 Forbidden test for authenticated but non-admin users.
Add rate limiting tests to validate 429 responses under bursts of requests.
Add tests to validate caching headers and actual cache invalidation signals on DELETE responses.
Add a concurrency test for deleting the same account simultaneously from multiple clients to check race conditions.
Add tests covering 500 Internal Server Error scenarios in addition to 503 for dependencies.
Add tests for trailing slash variations and idempotent behavior on repeated deletions.
Add basic observability tests to verify logs/metrics around delete operations.
